 active at dawn and dusk. The bird is also noted to be very adaptable, it can continue to live in land after agriculture begins, it only leaves lands when heavy human occupation begins. Call The call of a yellow-necked spurfowl is a series of scratchy descending upslurs, up to seven in a series. Male yellow-necked spurfowl often call while standing on top of mounds of earth or rock, often termite mounds. Conservation status The yellow-necked spurfowl is not in the threshold for vulnerable species despite the fact that its population (though unquantified) is thought to be in decline (though not at a fast rate). The primary threat to the species is over-hunting. Gallery References External links Xeno-canto: audio recordings of the yellow-necked spurfowl", "shortSummary": "The yellow-necked spurfowl or yellow-necked francolin (Pternistis leucoscepus) is a species of bird in the family Phasianidae. It is found…", "locations": ["吉布提", "厄立特里亚", "索马里", "苏丹", "乌干达"], "threats": ["猎捕压力"], "lat": 11.5, "lng": 43.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Francolin.jpg/960px-Francolin.jpg?utm_source=en.wikipedia.org&utm_campaign=api&utm_content=thumbnail", "order": "Galliformes", "family": "Phasianidae", "genus": "Pternistis", "species": "Pternistis leucoscepus", "orderCn": "鸡形目", "familyCn": "雉科", "genusCn": "鸡鹧鸪属", "speciesCn": "Yellow-necked spurfowl", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-galliformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-phasianidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-pternistis", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-pternistis-leucoscepus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-galliformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-phasianidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-pternistis", "species": "taxonomy-species-pternistis-leucoscepus"}, "expand